          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1689685527786-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1689685527786-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>mornay fish mix </strong>to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> (use individual ones for fancy presentation!) and top with your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong>, a little drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the dish[es] in the oven and cook for 18-22 min or until bubbling and golden and the fish is cooked through – this is your<strong> creamy cod & king prawn mornay</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1689685531909-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1689685531909-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1689685531909-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1689685531909-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1689685531909-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the mornay is nearly ready, reboil the kettle and return the reserved pot to a low heat with a little drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>dried oregano </strong>with the <strong>remaining grated garlic </strong>and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>drained potatoes</strong> to the pot with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and a little drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until very fragrant – these are your <strong>garlic & oregano potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1689685536254-x200.jpg",
